# Keep bash-executed and bash-generated files LF even on Windows checkouts.
# core.autocrlf=true materializes CRLF, which (a) breaks bash on the \r's
# ("$'\r': command not found") and (b) makes check-rls-grants-snapshot.sh
# falsely diff its LF database dump against a CRLF snapshot file.
*.sh text eol=lf
rls_grants_snapshot.txt text eol=lf
# css/output.css for the same class of reason: it is a committed build
# artefact, and CI's css-build-check rebuilds it and diffs against the
# committed copy. Tailwind always writes LF, so a CRLF checkout makes a
# local rebuild-and-diff report all ~2950 lines as changed when nothing
# about the content differs at all. CI (Linux, no autocrlf) was never
# affected - this is purely so the same check behaves sanely on Windows.
css/output.css text eol=lf
